abstracts.cdata!:
The Health Project is intended to
            improve and strengthen health services and planning. The
            primary objectives of this project are as follows. First,
            mortality and morbidity will be reduced. This is
            particularly intended for the 300,000 inhabitants of the
            predominantly rural Batinah region. Second, the
            Government's institutional capacity to plan and manage
            the health sector will be strengthened. Finally, efforts
            will be made to prepare the way for country wide
            implementation of a more efficient service delivery model.
